# 🏔️ Peak Finance

**Climb Higher. Spend Smarter.**

A modern, feature-rich personal finance PWA for iOS and Android. Track budgets, transactions, recurring bills, savings goals, and financial insights—all offline-capable with cloud sync.

## 🚀 Features

✅ **Budget Management** — Create monthly budgets by category with real-time tracking
✅ **Transaction Tracking** — Log income and expenses with merchant categorization
✅ **Recurring Bills** — Manage subscriptions and recurring payments
✅ **Savings Goals** — Set and track progress toward financial targets
✅ **Data Import** — Upload CSV/Excel files to bulk import transactions
✅ **Cloud Sync** — Supabase integration for real-time multi-device sync
✅ **Offline-First** — Works fully offline with IndexedDB + localStorage
✅ **Dark/Light Themes** — System-aware theming with manual override
✅ **PWA Installable** — Install as native app on iOS & Android home screens
✅ **Mobile-Optimized** — Touch-friendly, accessibility-first design

## 📱 Platform Support

- **iOS**: Safari "Add to Home Screen" (all iPhone models)
- **Android**: Chrome "Install App" (PWA manifest)
- **Web**: Works in all modern browsers (Chrome, Safari, Firefox, Edge)

## 🛠️ Installation & Deployment

### Local Development

```bash
# Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/ctrax68-hash/Peak-Finance.git
cd Peak-Finance

# Serve locally
python3 -m http.server 8000

# Visit
http://localhost:8000
```

### Deploy to Production

1. Upload all files to your web server (Vercel, Netlify, GitHub Pages, etc.)
2. Ensure HTTPS is enabled (required for PWA)
3. Test on real devices

### Required Files

```
├── index.html                    (Main app — 1.8 MB single file)
├── manifest.json                 (PWA metadata)
├── peak-finance-16x16.png        (Favicon)
├── peak-finance-32x32.png        (Favicon retina)
├── peak-finance-180x180.png      (iOS home screen)
├── peak-finance-192x192.png      (Android home screen)
├── peak-finance-512x512.png      (PWA splash/store)
└── peak-finance-1024x1024.png    (Promotional)
```

## 📖 Getting Started

### First Launch
1. Open the app in your browser
2. Complete the welcome tutorial (optional)
3. Set up your first budget
4. Start adding transactions

### Add to Home Screen

**iPhone (iOS)**
1. Open in Safari
2. Tap Share → "Add to Home Screen"
3. Name it "Peak Finance"
4. App launches fullscreen with no address bar

**Android**
1. Open in Chrome
2. Tap Menu (⋮) → "Install app"
3. App launches fullscreen as native PWA

### Import Data

1. Go to **Transactions** tab
2. Tap import icon
3. Upload CSV/Excel file with columns: Date, Merchant, Category, Amount
4. Map columns to fields
5. Review and confirm import

## 🏗️ Architecture

### Single-File PWA
- **No build tools required** — Pure HTML/CSS/JS
- **~1.8 MB** uncompressed, ~400 KB gzipped
- **~36,500 lines** of code
- **Vanilla JS** — no frameworks, no dependencies

### Storage

**Client-side (user device)**
- **IndexedDB** — Transaction history, budgets, goals
- **localStorage** — App settings, theme preference, user state

**Server-side (optional)**
- **Supabase** — Real-time sync, multi-device support, backup
- Fully functional without cloud (offline-first)

### Tech Stack

- **HTML5** — Semantic markup, form controls
- **CSS3** — Custom properties, grid/flexbox, animations
- **JavaScript (ES5)** — Broad device compatibility
- **PWA APIs** — Service Worker (planned), Web App Manifest, IndexedDB
- **Supabase** (optional) — PostgreSQL + real-time sync

